Systemd timers are the equivalent to cron but better.

Systemd timer lives in /etc/systemd/system/example.timer

Benefits of Systemd Timer:

    - Logging with Journald
    - Dependancy Handling
    - Service Supervision
    - Resource limits (CPU, Memory)
    - Restart limits
    - Extremely reliable

What does the systemd timer do? It defines what the triggers for the service is, whether it should be persistent, how often and when it should be run.

